Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @sweet potatoes{2} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a
large drizzle of @oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until tender
and slightly crispy, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Trim and discard woody bottom ends from @asparagus{6%oz}. Swap in asparagus for
sweet potatoes. Roast on top rack until lightly browned and tender, ~{8-10%minutes}.
(Reserve sweet potatoes for another use.)

Meanwhile, trim and mince @scallions{2}(trimmed and minced, whites separated from greens).
Peel @ginger{1%thumb} and grate using a #zester{} or the small holes of a
#box grater{} until you have ¾ tsp (1 1/2 tsp for 4 servings). Peel and mince or
grate @garlic{1%clove}(minced or grated).

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{4%tablespoon}, scallion greens, ¾ tsp
@soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, ¼ tsp grated ginger, ¼ tsp @sugar{1/4%teaspoon}, and a
pinch of garlic (use 1 1/2 tsp soy sauce, ½ tsp ginger, and ½ tsp sugar for 4
servings).

In a #large bowl{}, gently combine @ground beef{10%oz}, scallion whites, half the
remaining soy sauce (all for 4 servings), remaining grated ginger, and remaining
garlic.

Form into two patties (four patties for 4), each slightly wider than a
@potato buns{2}.

When sweet potatoes have 10 minutes left, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon}
in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add patties and cook to desired
doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

While burgers cook, halve and toast buns.

Spread cut sides of buns with aioli (save some for dipping), then fill with
patties, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%oz}, and @crispy fried onions{1}.

Divide burgers and sweet potato wedges between plates. Serve with remaining
aioli on the side for dipping.